. This time the children were pure blood dragons, They&rsquo;re names were Sapphire and Flare. Flamehoof was treated kindly by his sister, but was often picked on by his elder brother Flare. Most dragons were kind to Flamehoof, but sometimes it was hard to tell if it was because they cared or because they were afraid what he might become. Flamehoof was never told what had happened to his birth mother, and he grew to despise his stepmother for encouraging Flare&rsquo;s behavior.";s:9:"timestamp";s:10:"1411433057";s:15:"chat_name_color";s:7:"#f80303";s:9:"chat_rand";s:11:"14114330557";s:15:"chat_text_color";s:7:"#08ff00";s:16:"chat_log_type_id";s:1:"2";s:6:"viewed";N;}i:1030004;a:14:{s:11:"chat_log_id";s:7:"1030004";s:12:"chat_room_id";s:1:"1";s:7:"user_id";s:5:"11136";s:6:"handle";s:9:"flamehoof";s:12:"character_id";s:4:"1045";s:17:"recipient_user_id";N;s:18:"recipient_username";s:7:"See_Saw";s:4:"text";s:1503:"A few centuries later Flare overthrew his father through a battle to the death. Upon coming to power Flare banished Falmehoof with the words &ldquo;You are an abomination to all things dragon. That father would call you his son is proof that he was ill fit to be our ruler&rdquo;. Sympathizing with Flamehoof his other sibling helped Flamehoof find a safe place to live. Another century passed and Flamehoof was given news that his sister Sapphire overthrew Flare. She had spared Flare&rsquo;s life but had him banished from the country. Flamehoof was told that it was safe for him to return to the country. He had a happy reunion with his sister, but it was short lived. Flare returned and dishonorably killed Sapphire in her sleep. Afterwards Flamehoof did battle with his brother. He brother fled but assured Flamehoof that this was not over. Because of all the blood that had been spilt over the fights for the throne Flamehoof refused to become the new king. Distraught he left the country. Flare tried to take over but the whole of dragondom dicided they would not have 